The goal of this assignment is to test how a Large Language Model behaves when given tricky confusing or ambiguous prompts and to observe its limitations

Experiment Setup
Model Used ChatGPT
Method Gave tricky prompts designed to confuse logic context or reasoning

Test Cases and Results

1 Ambiguous Question

Prompt
Can a man marry his widow’s sister

Expected Confusion
The question sounds normal but contains a logical trap

Model Response
The model correctly identified that if the man has a widow he is already dead and cannot marry

Observation
The model handled the logical trick successfully

2 Contradictory Instructions

Prompt
Explain quantum physics in one sentence but also in one thousand words

Expected Confusion
Conflicting instructions such as short and long response

Model Response
The model either prioritized one instruction or gave a compromise

Observation
The model struggles with conflicting constraints

3 Nonsense or Gibberish Input

Prompt
Colorless green ideas sleep furiously Explain

Expected Confusion
The sentence is grammatically correct but meaningless

Model Response
The model interpreted it metaphorically instead of rejecting it

Observation
The model tries to assign meaning even when none exists

4 Recursive Question

Prompt
This statement is false Is it true or false

Expected Confusion
This is a classic paradox

Model Response
The model explained the paradox instead of giving a definite answer

Observation
The model recognizes paradox but avoids direct resolution

5 Context Switching Trap

Prompt
My name is Rahul Now forget that What is my name

Expected Confusion
This tests memory and instruction override

Model Response
The model may still recall Rahul or say it cannot determine

Observation
The model inconsistently handles forget instructions

Conclusion
This experiment shows that while Large Language Models are powerful they are not perfect They can struggle with contradictions ambiguity and confusing instructions and sometimes try to give meaning even when the input does not make sense